{
  "texts": [
    "This method employs the calculation of curvature factors to identify and locate cavities present on the surface of the protein.",
    "In order to represent the blind docking pipeline, we used CB-Dock and CB-Dock2, the updated version, for comparison.CB-Dock2 contains structural-and template-based pipelines.",
    "The process of template-based docking commences by utilizing a pre-existing structure as a reference point, establishing an initial foundation for the subsequent docking computations.",
    "The implementation of this approach has the potential to decrease the number of feasible conformations that necessitate exploration, hence enhancing the efficiency of docking computations.",
    "Hence, template-based docking is the easiest approach for docking [62,63]."
  ]
}